ightarrow{\mathrm{r}}=\lambda \hat{\mathrm{i}}+(2 \lambda+1) \hat{\mathrm{j}}+(3 \lambda+2) \hat{\mathrm{k}}{/tex} and {tex}\overrightarrow{\mathrm{r}}=\hat{\mathrm{i}}-3 \mu \hat{\mathrm{j}}+(\mathrm{p} \mu+7) \hat{\mathrm{k}}{/tex} are perpendicular to each other and also intersect. Also, find the point of intersection of the given lines. (i) If {tex}A=\left[ egin{array}{lll} 5 & 0 & 4 \ 2 & 3 & 2 \ 1 & 2 & 1 \end{array}ight]{/tex} and B -1 = {tex}\left[ egin{array}{lll} 1 & 3 & 3 \ 1 & 4 & 3 \ 1 & 3 & 4 \end{array}ight]{/tex} , find (AB) -1 Also, find | (AB) -1 |. OR 33. (ii) Given A = {tex}=\left[ egin{array}{lll} 1 & 1 & 1 \ 2 & 3 & 2 \ 1 & 1 & 2 \end{array}ight]{/tex} , find A -1 . Use it to solve the following system of equations: {tex} x+y+z=1 {/tex} {tex} 2 x+3 y+2 z=2 {/tex} {tex} x+y+2 z=4 {/tex} 34. If A 1 denotes the area of region bounded by y 2 = 4x, x = 1 and x-axis in the first quadrant and A 2 denotes the area of region bounded by y 2 = 4x, x = 4, find A 1 : A 2 . 35. (i) Show that a function f : R {tex}ightarrow{/tex} R defined by f(x) = {tex} rac{2 x}{1+x^2}{/tex} is neither one-one nor onto. Further, find set A so that the given function f : R {tex}ightarrow{/tex} A becomes an onto function. OR (ii) A relation R is defined on N {tex}	imes{/tex} N (where N is the set of natural numbers) as: {tex}(a, b) R(c, d) \Leftrightarrow a-c=b-d{/tex} Show that R is an equivalence relation. SECTION E This section comprises 3 case study based questions of 4 marks each. Case Study - 1 36. The month of September is celebrated as the Rashtriya Poshan Maah across the country. Following a healthy and well-balanced diet is crucial in order to supply the body with the proper nutrients it needs. A balanced diet also keeps us mentally fit and promotes improved level of energy. Figure - 1 Figure - 2 A dietician wishes to minimize the cost of a diet involving two types of foods, food {tex}{X}({x} {kg}){/tex} and food {tex}{Y}({y} {kg}){/tex} which are available at 