Annual Exam - 2024 Code: 65/2/2 (set-2) Please check that this question paper contains 23 printed pages. Please check that this question paper contains 38 questions. Q.P. Code given on the right hand side of the question paper should be written on the title page of the answer-book by the candidate. Please write down the serial number of the question in the answer-book before attempting it. 15 minute time has been allotted to read this question paper. The question paper will be distributed at 10.15 a.m. From 10.15 a.m. to 10.30 a.m., the students will read the question paper only and will not write any answer on the answer-book during this period. MATHEMATICS Time allowed:3 hours Maximum Marks:80 General Instructions : Read the following instructions very carefully and strictly follow them: This question paper contains 38 questions. All questions are compulsory . This question paper is divided into five Sections - A, B, C, D and E . In Section A, Questions no. 1 to 18 are multiple choice questions (MCQs) and questions number 19 and 20 are Assertion-Reason based questions of 1 mark each. In Section B, Questions no. 21 to 25 are very short answer (VSA) type questions, carrying 2 marks each. In Section C, Questions no. 26 to 31 are short answer (SA) type questions, carrying 3 marks each. In Section D, Questions no. 32 to 35 are long answer (LA) type questions carrying 5 marks each. In Section E, Questions no. 36 to 38 are case study based questions carrying 4 marks each. There is no overall choice. However, an internal choice has been provided in 2 questions in Section B, 3 questions in Section C, 2 questions in Section D and 2 questions in Section E. Use of calculators is not allowed. SECTION A This section comprises multiple choice questions (MCQs) of 1 mark each. 1. The number of solutions of differential equation {tex} rac{dy}{dx}-y=1{/tex} , given that y(0) = 1, is: a. 0 b. 1 c. 2 d. infinitely many Correct Answer: (b) 1 Explanation: The differential equation {tex} rac{d y}{d x}-y=1{/tex} is a first-order linear equation. Its general solution is {tex}y(x)=C e^x+e^x-1{/tex} . Given the initial condition {tex}y(0)=1{/tex} , we find {tex}C=0{/tex} . Thus, there is exactly one solution: {tex}y(x)=e^x-1{/tex} . The answer is 1 . 1 2. For any two vectors {tex}\overrightarrow{\mathrm{a}}{/tex} and {tex}\overrightarrow{\mathrm{b}}{/tex} which of the following statements is always true? a. {tex} \overrightarrow{{a}} \cdot \overrightarrow{{~b}} \geq|\overrightarrow{{a}}||\overrightarrow{{b}}|{/tex} b. {tex} \overrightarrow{{a}} \cdot \overrightarrow{{~b}}=|\overrightarrow{{a}}||\overrightarrow{{b}}|{/tex} c. {tex} \vec{a} \cdot \vec{b} \leq|\vec{a}||\vec{b}|{/tex} d. {tex} \vec{a} \cdot \vec{b}<|\vec{a}||\vec{b}|{/tex} Correct Answer: (c) {tex} \vec{a} \cdot \vec{b} \leq|\vec{a}||\vec{b}|{/tex} Explanation: The correct answer is {tex}\vec{a} \cdot \vec{b} \leq|\vec{a}||\vec{b}|{/tex} . This follows from the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality, which states that the dot product of two vectors is less than or equal to the product of their magnitudes. Equality holds only when the vectors are parallel. 1 3. The coordinates of the foot of the perpendicular drawn from the point (0, 1, 2) on the x-axis are given by: a. (1, 0, 0) b. (2, 0, 0) c. {tex} (\sqrt{5}, 0,0){/tex} d. (0, 0, 0) Correct Answer: (d) (0, 0, 0) Explanation: The foot of the perpendicular from the point (0, 1, 2) to the x-axis has the same x-coordinate (0) but zero y and z-coordinates. Thus, the coordinates are (0, 0, 0) 1 4. The common region determined by all the constraints of a linear programming problem is called: a. an unbounded region b. an optimal region c. a bounded region d. a feasible region Correct Answer: (d) a feasible region Explanation: a feasible region 1 5. Let E be an event of a sample space S of an experiment, then P(S|E) = a. {tex} {P}({~S} \cap {E}){/tex} b. P(E) c. 1 d. 0 Correct Answer: (c) 1 Explanation: The conditional probability {tex}P(S \mid E){/tex} represents the probability of the sample space {tex}S{/tex} given event {tex}E{/tex} . Since {tex}S{/tex} is the entire sample space, it always occurs, leading to: {tex} P(S \mid E)=1{/tex} Thus, the correct answer is 1. 1 6. The number of all scalar matrices of order 3, with each entry -1, 0 or 1, is: a. 1 b. 3 c. 2 d. 39 Correct Answer: (b) 3 Explanation: A scalar matrix of order 3 has the form cI, where I is the identity matrix and c is a constant Given c can be -1, 0, or 1 , there are 3 distinct scalar matrices: -I, 0 and I. Therefore, the answer is 3. 1 7. {tex} rac{d}{d x}\left[\cos \left(\log x+e^xight)ight] 	ext { at } x=1{/tex} is: a. -sin e b. sin e c. -(1 + e) sin e d. (1 + e) sin e Correct Answer: (c) -(1 + e) sin e Explanation: To find {tex} rac{d}{d x}\left[\cos \left(\log x+e^xight)ight]{/tex} at {tex}x=1{/tex} , use the chain rule: {tex}  rac{d}{d x}=-\sin \left(\log x+e^xight) \cdot\left( rac{1}{x}+e^xight) .{/tex} At {tex}x=1, \log 1=0{/tex} and {tex}e^1=e{/tex} , so the expression simplifies to {tex}-\sin e \cdot(1+e){/tex} . Thus, the answer is {tex}-(1+e) \sin e{/tex} . 1 8. The degree of the differential equation {tex}\left(y^{\prime \prime}ight)^2+\left(y^{\prime}ight)^3=x \sin \left(y^{\prime}ight){/tex} is: a. 1 b. 2 c. 3 d. not defined Correct Answer: (d) not defined Explanation: {tex}\left(y^{\prime \prime}ight)^2+\left(y^{\prime}ight)^3=x \sin \left(\cdot y^{\prime}ight){/tex} is. {tex} ecause{/tex} it is not diff eq. {tex}	herefore{/tex} degree of diff is undefined / Not defined 1 9. The unit vector perpendicular to both vectors {tex}\hat{i}+\hat{k} 	ext { and } \hat{i}-\hat{k}{/tex} is: a. {tex} 2 \hat{j}{/tex} b. {tex} \hat{j}{/tex} c. {tex}  rac{\hat{i}-\hat{k}}{\sqrt{2}}{/tex} d. {tex}  rac{\hat{i}+\hat{k}}{\sqrt{2}}{/tex} Correct Answer: (b) {tex} \hat{j}{/tex} Explanation: To find a unit vector perpendicular to both {tex}\hat{i}+\hat{k}{/tex} and {tex}\hat{i}-\hat{k}{/tex} , we use the cross product: {tex} (\hat{i}+\hat{k}) 	imes(\hat{i}-\hat{k})=\hat{j}(-1-1)=-2 \hat{j}{/tex} The unit vector is {tex}  rac{-2 \hat{j}}{2}=-\hat{j}{/tex} Thus, the correct answer is {tex}\hat{j}{/tex} . 1 10. Direction ratios of a vector parallel to line {tex} rac{x-1}{2}=-y= rac{2 z+1}{6}{/tex} are: a. 2, -1, 6 b. 2, 1, 6 c. 2, 1, 3 d. 2, -1, 3 Correct Answer: (d) 2, -1, 3 Explanation: The given equation of the line is: {tex}  rac{x-1}{2}=-y= rac{2 z+1}{6}{/tex} This represents the parametric form of the line. We can break this down into parametric equations by introducing a parameter {tex}t{/tex} : {tex}  rac{x-1}{2}=t \Rightarrow x=2 t+1 {/tex} {tex} -y=t \Rightarrow y=-t {/tex} {tex}  rac{2 z+1}{6}=t \Rightarrow 2 z+1=6 t \Rightarrow z=3 t- rac{1}{2} {/tex} Thus, the parametric equations are: {tex} x=2 t+1, y=-t, z=3 t- rac{1}{2}{/tex} The direction ratios of the vector parallel to the line are the coefficients of {tex}t{/tex} in the parametric equations. Therefore, the direction ratios are: {tex} 	ext { Direction ratios }=(2,-1,3){/tex} So, the correct answer is: 2, -1, 3. 1 11. If F(x) = {tex}\left[ egin{array}{ccc} \cos x & -\sin x & 0 \ \sin x & \cos x & 0 \ 0 & 0 & 1 \end{array}ight]{/tex} and [F(x)] 2 = F(kx), then the value of k is: a. 1 b. 2 c. 0 d. -2 Correct Answer: (b) 2 Explanation: To find {tex}k{/tex} such that {tex}[F(x)]^2=F(k x){/tex} , we compute {tex}[F(x)]^2{/tex} : {tex} [F(x)]^2=F(x) F(x)=\left[ egin{array}{ccc} \cos ^2 x-\sin ^2 x & -2 \sin x \cos x & 0 \ 2 \sin x \cos x & \cos ^2 x-\sin ^2 x & 0 \ 0 & 0 & 1 \end{array}ight]=F(2 x){/tex} Thus, {tex}k=2{/tex} . The correct answer is 2. 1 12. If a line makes an angle of 30 o with the positive direction of x-axis, 120 o with the positive direction of y-axis, then the angle which it makes with the positive direction of z-axis is: a. 90o b. 120o c. 60o d. 0o Correct Answer: (a) 90o Explanation: To find the angle with the z-axis, we use the relation: {tex} \cos ^2 \alpha+\cos ^2  eta+\cos ^2 \gamma=1{/tex} where {tex}\alpha=30^{\circ}{/tex} and {tex} eta=120^{\circ}{/tex} . Calculating, we get: {tex} \cos ^2 30^{\circ}= rac{3}{4}, \cos ^2 120^{\circ}= rac{1}{4}{/tex} Thus, {tex}  rac{3}{4}+ rac{1}{4}+\cos ^2 \gamma=1 \Longrightarrow \cos ^2 \gamma=0 \Longrightarrow \gamma=90^{\circ} .{/tex} So, the angle with the z-axis is 90 o . 1 13. If the sum of all the elements of a 3 {tex}	imes{/tex} 3 scalar matrix is 9, then the product of all its elements is: a. 0 b. 9 c. 27 d. 729 Correct Answer: (a) 0 Explanation: {tex} 	ext { Let Scalar Marrix. }{/tex} {tex}\left[ egin{array}{lll} k & 0 & 0 \ 0 & k & 0 \ 0 & 0 & k \end{array}ight]{/tex} {tex} 	ext { ATP, } {/tex} {tex} 	ext { sum }=3 K {/tex} {tex} 3 K=9 {/tex} {tex} K=3 {/tex} {tex} 	ext { Product }=0 	imes 27=0 {/tex} {tex} .=	ext {. } {/tex} 1 14. Which of the following statements is not true about equivalence classes A i (i = 1, 2, ...n) formed by an equivalence relation R defined on a set A? a. {tex}  igcup_\limits{i=1}^n A_i=A{/tex} b. {tex} {A}_{{i}} \cap {~A}_{{j}} 
